Dr. Gerald Seiler, Research Botanist (Adjunct Professor, Dept. of Plant Sciences, NDSU) seilerg@fargo.ars.usda.gov; (701) 239-1380
This project emphasizes the collection of additional populations of wild sunflower species to obtain a greater genetic diversity of the genus Helianthus.
Interrelationships of species are investigated using biosystematic approaches to delineate and clarify taxonomic affinities among and between wild sunflower species.
Wild species and interspecific germplasms are evaluated as a source of genes for agronomic characteristics for the improvement of cultivated sunflower.
